node.text:
How to Balayage Redhead 👩‍🦰 

My model at my recent #TripleThreatFoilayage class was a redhead with a level 6 permanent tint. 

I wanted to add dimension without taking her too blonde for her completion. I wanted the look of open air painting but needed foils to lift through the tint. 

After shaping up her Haircut 💇‍♀️ 
I taught my signature technique of breaking down brick 🧱 layered Balayage Triangles 🔼 into 3 foils each ( Triple Threat 😘 ) and added auburn lowlights in-between. 

Then I ColorMelted with an Auburn Shadow Root and Strawberry 🍓 Blonde 👱‍♀️ Gloss 

Formulas:

Lightener @oligopro Cool Blonde 👱‍♀️ & @olaplex 💦 

Lowlights @schwarzkopfusa TBH 5-47 & 8-47 1:1 13vol

ColorMelt @schwarzkopfusa TBH

Root 5-47 + 6-06 + 6-19  1:1:1 6vol and Tone Softener 

Hairline- Mids-Ends 10-56 + 9-47
1:1:1 13vol and Tone Softener

Would you believe me if I told you this was only 42 Foils that can be applied in 1 Hour ?!? 

Foilayage can be a frustratingly long technique and can easily take well over 100 foils and up to 3 hours to apply. I know, I’ve been there 😪

Over-foiling and ending up with a Rootie Platinum is hard not to do. 

Foilayage is supposed to be Balayage inside of Foils for the same visual placement with a lighter lift. If you think about it, we paint open-air on large triangles and can therefore apply a Balayage in about an hour.

I had the idea 💡 of breaking the Round Headshape into inter-locking Triangles, like a Geodesic Dome, and applying 2 Foils per Triangle 📐 One foil to replicate the surface painting and One Foil to replicate the Ombre tip out 🤯

#GeodesicFoilayage 

It’s surprisingly high impact with minimal foils! All the brightness is on the top surface and through the ends and all the depth is underneath for internal dimension 🤓

Ever struggled with Tint Bands?

This was my recent Live Demonstration model for my #GeodesicFoilayage class and she had a level 6 tint Ban with some traditional highlights.

Tips:
1. Break up the Line of Demarcation with Teasie-Lights to both pick out the dark as well as add gradience or Ombré through the ends
2. After 45mins processing, scrape off the old lightener and re-apply fresh to the areas that still need lift
3. Try a permanent Basebreaker in your ColorMelt formula starting at the line of demarcation to push out artificial pigment molecules and oxidize the natural pigment under the tint 🤯 ( Color cannot lift color, but it can “affect it” )

Formulas 🎨 

Lightener @oligopro Cool Blonde with @olaplex 💦 

ColorMelt @schwarzkopfusa TBH
Roots 1/4th 6-06 & 3/4ths 7-16
1:1:1 6vol and Tone Softener

Inspo: 90’s Cindy Crawford ( You Know - the @pepsi Commercial )

Tips:

1. Do Chunky pick up at the hairline and then a Finer Weave directly behind
2. Use 3 Large Circular Sections and Over-Direct hair Forward to create Round Ombre’
3. Tease first and then Weave for an extremely blended tip out with the @3dbalayage Comb and @ashleenormanhair Foilayage Boards 
4. Gloss all the hair first and while it processes, tap a darker level at the roots of the hairline for a subtle shadow 

Formulas:
Hairline @oligopro Lightening Creme
Ombré @oligopro Cool Blonde
Gloss @oligopro Calura Gloss 9NB 10V 9G
Hairline Shadow @oligopro 7N 7AI 

Makeup 💄 @muyvette 
Host @desertbeautynv 
Foils @styletekbeauty

node.text:
“I’ll Be Back... Next Time with a TEAM”

Summer 2018 I was 4 months Postpartum from my second child 👶 and attended @oneshothairawards for the first time with my Husband and my Breast Pump 🤱 😅

I was nominated for Color Transformation on a Class Demonstration Model I taught cross country at 36 weeks Pregnant 🤰

Although I didn’t win, I was very Inspired 🤩 Mostly by the TEAMs that traveled together to support their Nominees ❤️
At the time, I had been in my Studio for about a year and a half after leaving my home salon of 11 years of which I was the Salon Educator of for most of those years. It was a Bitter Sweet time of Transition for me as I left a Team I had spent a Decade to help build to go out on my own at the same time as expanding my little family 👨‍👩‍👧‍👦

At times it was Scary 😱 and Lonely 😰 but I put my trust in God’s Plan 🙏

I got into Education in 2007 as my Salon’s Bumble and Bumble Network Educator 👩‍🏫 because I wanted to be a part of something BIGGER than Myself.

As I sat in the audience of BTC show, right before my category’s winner was announced, I told myself “I’m not ready but I will be Back! And Next Time it will be with a TEAM”

Summer 2019 @colorbycares & @muyvette and I got together for the first time and our Ginger Shag went Viral 🔥 
We collaborated again in November and AGAIN our creations Exploded 💥 
Submitting together in the #btconeshot2020_collaboration was a Dream Come True 😭 
Summer 2020 was supposed to be our moment … and we know how that went 😪

But… We didn’t stop 🛑 💪
I continued to travel and teach and collaborate whenever and wherever I could and grew my Team 💃🏼

Across the Board my Team, including:
@am_hairstylist
@graysontroy @lightenuptheworld @josh_thebalayboy 
got 12 Top 🔝 💯 Nominations 🏆🏆🏆🏆🏆🏆🏆🏆🏆🏆🏆🏆

And we now have 6 Top🔝 25 🏆🏆🏆🏆🏆🏆

I couldn’t be more proud 🥲 as this Validates my Mission and Purpose to not just elevate myself, but to make an Impact with my Team for our Industry! The Sky’s the Limit ✈️ 🚀

See you all in Austin, TEXAS @anh_crew 🍾 🥂 🎉 

@behindthechair_com
